!!!
%html{:lang => "en"}
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html; charset=UTF-8", "http-equiv" => "content-type"}/
  %body
    %div{"data-role" => "page"}
      %div{"data-role" => "header"}
        %h1 jQuery.fx.off
      %div{"data-role" => "content", "data-theme" => "c", :id => "jQuery.fx.off1"}
        %h2.jq-clearfix.roundTop.section-title
          %span.name jQuery.fx.off
          %span.returns
            Returns:
            %a.return{:href => "http://docs.jquery.com/Types#Boolean"} Boolean
        .entry-details
          %p.desc
            %strong> Description:
            Globally disable all animations.
          %ul.signatures
            %li.signature{:id => "jQuery.fx.off"}
              %h4.name
                %span.versionAdded>
                  version added:
                  %a{:href => "/category/version/1.3/"} 1.3
                jQuery.fx.off
          .longdesc
            %p
              When this property is set to
              = succeed "," do
                %code true
              all animation methods will immediately set elements to their final state when called, rather than displaying an effect. This may be desirable for a couple reasons:
            %ul
              %li jQuery is being used on a low-resource device.
              %li
                Users are encountering accessibility problems with the animations (see the article
                %a{:href => "http://www.jdeegan.phlegethon.org/turn_off_animation.html"} Turn Off Animation
                for more information).
            %p
              Animations can be turned back on by setting the property to
              = succeed "." do
                %code false
          %h3 Example:
          #entry-examples.entry-examples
            #example-0
              %h4
                %span.desc Toggle animation on and off
              %pre
                %code.example.demo-code
                  :preserve
                    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                    &lt;html&gt;
                    &lt;head&gt;
                      &lt;style&gt;
                        div { width:50px; height:30px; margin:5px; float:left;
                              background:green; }
                        &lt;/style&gt;
                      &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/head&gt;
                    &lt;body&gt;
                    	&lt;p&gt;&lt;input type="button" value="Run"/&gt; &lt;button&gt;Toggle fx&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
                    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
                    &lt;script&gt;
                    var toggleFx = function() {
                      $.fx.off = !$.fx.off;
                    };
                    toggleFx();
                    
                    $("button").click(toggleFx)
                    
                    $("input").click(function(){
                      $("div").toggle("slow");
                    });
                      &lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/body&gt;
                    &lt;/html&gt;              %h4 Demo:
              .demo.code-demo
